df_original = rbind(a,b)
# created_at will preserve the specific time
df_original$created_at = as.POSIXlt(df_original$created_at, format = "%a %b %d %H:%M:%S %z %Y")
df_original$created_date = as.POSIXlt(strftime(as.POSIXlt(df_original$created_at, format = "%a %b %d %H:%M:%S %z %Y"), format = "%Y-%m-%d"), format = "%Y-%m-%d")

# the new data has a differently formatted creation date column

remove(a)

# remove duplicate tweets, while only keeping the tweet with maximum retweet_count

df_unique <- df_original %>%
  group_by(original_text) %>%
  slice(which.max(retweet_count)) %>%
  ungroup()

# remove "RT @username:" substring from the original tweet 
df_unique$edited_tweet <- sub( "RT @(\\w+):*", "", df_unique$original_text)

# Create a new column for storing bool info if the strings match

df_unique$contains_kw <- grepl("coronavirus|covid 19|covid-19|covid19|corona virus|#CCPVirus|#ChinaDidThis|#ChinaLiedPeopleDied|#ChinaVirus|#ChineseVirus|chinese virus|#ChineseBioterrorism|#FuckChina|#KungFlu|#MakeChinaPay|#wuhanflu|#wuhanvirus|wuhan virus|wuhanvirus|KungFlu|china virus|chinesevirus|chink|chinky|chonky|churka|cina|cokin|communistvirus|coolie|dink|niakoue|pastel de flango|slant|slant eye|slopehead|ting tong|yokel|#IAmNotAVirus|#WashTheHate|#RacismIsAVirus|#IAmNotCovid19|#BeCool2Asians|#StopAAPIHate|#ActToChange|#HateIsAVirus|wuhan", df_unique$edited_tweet)

  select(id,processed_tweet)%>%
  group_by(id)%>%

  inner_join(afinn)%>%
  summarize(TweetSentiment = mean(value))%>%
  ungroup()%>%
  summarize(min=min(TweetSentiment),
            max=max(TweetSentiment),
            median=median(TweetSentiment),
            mean=mean(TweetSentiment))

sentiment_scores = sentiment_scores %>% rename(word=term) %>%
  inner_join(afinn) %>%
  group_by(document) %>%
  summarize(sentiment_score = sum(value)) %>%
  ungroup()
## Joining, by = "word"

    sentiment_score == 0 ~ "Neutral",
    sentiment_score > 0 & sentiment_score <= 4 ~ "Moderately positive",
    sentiment_score > 4 ~ "Strongly positive"

# Date reformatting
library(stringr)

mm <- function(month){
  if (month == "Apr"){
    return ("04")
  }
  else if (month == "May"){
    return ("05")
  }
  else if (month == "Jun"){
    return ("06")
  }
  else if (month == "Jul"){
    return ("07")
  }
  else if (month == "Aug"){
    return ("08")
  }
  else if (month == "Sep"){
    return ("09")
  }
  else if (month == "Oct"){
    return ("10")
  }
}
reformatter <- function(datestr){
  y = substr(str_match(datestr, " \\d{4}\\b")[1,1],start=2,stop=5)
  m = mm(substr(str_match(datestr, " \\b\\w{3}\\b"),start=2,stop=4)[1,1])
  d = substr(str_match(datestr, " \\d{2}\\b")[1,1],start=2,stop=3)
  return (paste(y, m, d, sep = "/", collapse = "/"))
}
